						<h3><b>Organizations Involved in Fair Trade</b></h3>

						<p>There are a variety of organizations that participate in the Fair Trade movement. The first groups were Ten Thousand Villages and SERRV International, which began in the United States, and Oxfam International, which started in England. The major organizations currently involved in Fair Trade include the original three, plus the World Fair Trade Organization, Global Exchange, the European Fair Trade Association, and Fair Trade USA. Fair Trade certification entities are also a critically important part of the movement, and they include FLO-CERT, Eco-Social/IBD and Fair Trade International.</p>
